\chapter{OneDrive and SharePoint files}

We want to read and write files stored in KTH's OneDrive and SharePoint
sites. The first constraint is authentication: we do not want to require a
separate Entra application registration or a client identifier just to move a
file.

The project already has a browser-like login stack through [[ladok3]] and
[[weblogin]]. We therefore reuse that authenticated session and talk to
SharePoint's classic REST endpoints instead of Microsoft Graph. This keeps the
command line workflow close to what already works elsewhere in the package.


\section{Code overview}

This module becomes [[kthutils.onedrive]]. We add a small session wrapper,
helpers for turning browser URLs into SharePoint REST paths, and two commands:
[[get]] and [[put]].
