The main resolver accepts ordinary file URLs and the more verbose copy-link
style URLs that Microsoft 365 places in the browser address bar.
<<functions>>=
def parse_sharepoint_url(url: str) -> SharePointLocation:
  """Resolve a browser URL into SharePoint REST coordinates."""
  parsed = urllib.parse.urlsplit(url)
  if not parsed.scheme or not parsed.netloc:
    raise ValueError(f"Unsupported OneDrive URL: {url}")

  server_relative_path = _extract_server_relative_path(parsed.path)
  if server_relative_path.endswith("/"):
    raise ValueError("The URL must address one file, not a folder.")

  return SharePointLocation(
      site_url=_build_site_url(parsed, server_relative_path),
      server_relative_path=server_relative_path)
@

We first normalise the path part of the browser URL. Copy links such as
[[/:w:/r/personal/...]] contain an extra marker segment that should not reach
the REST API, while direct file URLs already use the server-relative path.
Classic [[Doc.aspx]] URLs do not reveal the file path, so we reject them with a
clear instruction instead of guessing.
<<functions>>=
def _extract_server_relative_path(path: str) -> str:
  """Return the server-relative file path embedded in ``path``."""
  decoded_path = urllib.parse.unquote(path)
  if decoded_path.lower().endswith("/doc.aspx"):
    raise ValueError(
        "Doc.aspx URLs do not expose the file path. Use a copy link or a "
        "direct file URL instead.")

  match = COPY_LINK_RE.match(decoded_path)
  if match:
    return match.group(1)

  for prefix in SERVER_RELATIVE_PATH_PREFIXES:
    if decoded_path.startswith(prefix):
      return decoded_path

  raise ValueError(f"Unsupported OneDrive URL path: {decoded_path}")
@

The site URL is the stable prefix that owns the document library. For personal
OneDrive URLs we keep [[/personal/<user>]], while team sites keep
[[/sites/<name>]] or [[/teams/<name>]]. The remaining path segments belong to
the library and folders, not the site itself.
<<functions>>=
def _build_site_url(parsed, server_relative_path: str) -> str:
  """Return the SharePoint site URL for ``server_relative_path``."""
  parts = server_relative_path.lstrip("/").split("/")
  if len(parts) < 2 or parts[0] not in SHAREPOINT_SITE_ROOTS:
    raise ValueError(
        f"Unsupported SharePoint path: {server_relative_path}")

  site_path = f"/{parts[0]}/{parts[1]}"
  return urllib.parse.urlunsplit((parsed.scheme,
                                  parsed.netloc,
                                  site_path,
                                  "",
                                  ""))
@

These constants capture the supported URL shapes in one place.
<<constants>>=
COPY_LINK_RE = re.compile(r"^/:[^:]+:/[a-z](/.*)$", re.IGNORECASE)
SERVER_RELATIVE_PATH_PREFIXES = (
    "/personal/",
    "/sites/",
    "/teams/",
)
SHAREPOINT_SITE_ROOTS = ("personal", "sites", "teams")
@

Parsing is easy to get subtly wrong, so we verify the supported cases directly.
